Reigning African Footballer of the Year Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang was named on Tuesday on a shortlist of five candidates for the 2016 award.The Gabon captain, whose goals for Borussia Dortmund have made him one of Europe&#8217;s most prolific strikers, is up against Algerians Riyad Mahrez and Islam Slimani who play for English champions Leicester CitySenegal and Liverpool forward Sadio Mane and AS Roma&#8217;s Egyptian winger Mohamed Salah were also nominated.Votes from the national team coaches or technical directors of the Confederation of African Football&#8217;s 54 members, plus a specially appointed panel of 10 experts, will determine the winner.The three finalists will be named in December before the award ceremony in Abuja, Nigeria on Jan. 5.-Reuters